{"type": "article", "id": 22796, "title": "在寸土寸金的东京，这家人还是保留了一个小花园", "description": "一个像方盒子一样的极简住宅。", "date": "2016-02-24T17:20:33Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 7137, "name": "东京"}, {"id": 14006, "name": "住宅设计"}, {"id": 23920, "name": "Elding Oscarson"}], "category": 17, "author": 161922, "comment_count": 12, "praise_count": 256, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702122349I0arTjKiZSdEwnul.jpeg", "contents": "\n\n<p>          </p>\n<p>在东京的一片住宅区，一个新建的方盒子一定能引起过路人的注意。它的外面由玻璃和木条组成，两两相间，让整体建筑显得简洁而轻盈。房子的旁边有一块长条形的绿化地，隐约能看到屋顶上的盆栽和屋内的场景，像是处于自然的环境中。区别与周围带有青瓦的传统民居和现代集合住宅。</p>\n<p>委托人是一对夫妇，他们最大的要求是尽可能保留旁边小花园，它有 35 年的历史，在周围住宅密集的地方显得稀有。这块地其实只有100 平米，但令设计方 Elding Oscarson 难办的倒不是面积小，而是不明确的委托，这对夫妇想要将这里作为周末度假的地方，而他们在东京或国外的小孩也来偶尔来这里暂住。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122341ovYciS0NAUhJ7m39.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122341TRhGYwK8SUCpONAr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122342az3u45h0qjbmx78P.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.65925926\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122342U1uryaVW0tETsDjk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<p class=\"\">Elding Oscarson 是一家来自瑞典的建筑事务所，他们做了很多日本的项目，拥有“干净、简练和成熟的风格”。设计师希望这里成为“一个被光与自然充分包围的地方”，不同于日本住宅将空间分割的传统做法，他们更倾向采用开放式的方式，给房子留一些大的空间。</p>\n<p class=\"\">一楼的一半空间是卧室，其余地方分布了卫生间、储物间和楼梯，二楼集中于起居室、餐厅和开放式的厨房，都没有分割开来，三楼则是一个完全平坦的方形露台。室内设计延续了室外的简洁干净，以白色和原木色为主，让空间开阔而清新自然。<br></p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122343RBSjuwNy9sf0rtdI.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">一楼入口（左）卫生间（右）</div></figcaption></figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122343KINaDQvGBzC026Yl.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">一楼卧室</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122344KLQ3sehE2zjg49bB.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66388889\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">二楼起居室</div></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122344AfktbUY5OpD0symr.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">二楼起居室</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122345xsWfpPkFizXV0SRy.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">二楼到三楼楼梯间</div></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122346IqofY30hNKMG1mxO.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">三楼露台</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div>\n<p>执意保留小花园说明委托人对自然的重视，Elding Oscarson 通过落地玻璃更进一步将自然引入室内。一楼其实是下沉式的，露出地面的正好是一圈可 360 度观景的玻璃窗，可以看到周围的花园和街道。二楼也是如此。小花园也可以作为社区停车的地方。尽管建筑有些奇特，这种做法并不突兀，wallpaper 称这所房子有着<a href=\"http://www.wallpaper.com/architecture/nerima-house-by-elding-oscarson-combines-the-best-of-swedish-and-japanese-architecture#144166\">“北欧式的简洁和日式的温暖”</a>。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122346RGqxFsAaQcCS5m2e.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.21506683\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122347dYj95Ueax6biVFPW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.34952767\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021223471pEbHtAznf5hKDFI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.34408602\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122348k7Il2QfSmACPoayE.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.07526882\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">一楼</div></figcaption></figure><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702122348ZjN93idfgavQyPSs.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.01832994\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">二楼</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021223480eDEBf3UgAFXOCQb.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.89166667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">三楼</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021223492M1alnWPghROiGzU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.71203704\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p class=\"\">图片来自 <a href=\"http://www.archdaily.com/781137/nerima-house-elding-oscarson\">archdaily</a></p>\n\n"}